iterates his reason for accepting the power of Link Joker after defeating <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Aichi, who is on his knees and screaming as he fights the effects of Reverse.</span></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KickTheSonOfABitch" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KickTheSonOfABitch">Kick the Son of a Bitch</a>: Ren is implied to do so. It's complicated. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> After Kyou's loss to Kai after the guy had spent pretty much all his screentime being an obnoxious, arrogant brat, it's very implied that Ren does something to him which leaves the guy a trembling, speechless wreck cowering on a bench. And Tetsu later says that Kyou has been sent back to headquarters for 'retraining'.</span><ul><li> Kicked some more by Tetsu and Asaka: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">first Tetsu tells him Foo Fighter has no need for losers and revokes his membership, then Asaka tells him he lacks ability and to get out.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HumiliationConga" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HumiliationConga">Kicked even more</a> by <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Aichi, in episodes 41 and 42</span>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KnightInShiningArmor" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KnightInShiningArmor">Knight in Shining Armor</a>: Aichi's Deck-Type, Royal Paladin, is this, mostly.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KnightOfCerebus" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KnightOfCerebus">Knight of Cerebus</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Ren's</span> appearance in season 1 introduces the person who will <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers